    <body>
        <p>In the Advanced view of the Stylesheet Editor <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineOnly,Snippets.Snippet10">(see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Flare/Interface/UI-Elements/Stylesheet-Editor.htm">Stylesheet Editor</MadCap:xref> and <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Flare/Styles/Editing-Styles.htm">Editing Styles in a Regular Stylesheet</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>, you can associate a condition with a style by using the <span class="Emphasis">mc-conditions</span> property<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.OnlineOnly,Snippets.Snippet12"> (see <MadCap:xref href="../../../../Flare/Conditions/About-Condition-Tags.htm">About Conditions</MadCap:xref>)</MadCap:conditionalText>. If you are viewing properties by group (rather than alphabetically) in the Stylesheet Editor, you can find this property in the Unclassified group.</p>
        <p>
            <img src="../../../Images/Flare/conditions_styles1.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
        </p>
        <p>If you hover over this property, a tool tip shows the names of the conditions that have been set on it.</p>
        <p>
            <img src="../../../Images/Flare/conditions_styles2.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
        </p>
    </body>
